item.title: U.S. Stocks Are Breaking Records. The Rest of the World Is Doing Better.
item.description: The U.S. stock market has shattered dozens of records this year. It still trails the rest of the world. Mounting concern about the U.S. economy’s growth prospects and a continuing trade war have led more investors to look beyond America’s shores for stocks at attractive prices. In fact, those international stocks are on pace to outperform their U.S. counterparts by the widest margin in 16 years.
